         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14/4/78. ¶  ¶ This day, dear Mr Bailey, I got your little package. ¶  ¶ The supposed Caesia is Arthropodium paniculatum, RBr, a species not previously found in Q.L. ¶  ¶ As regards the grasses, it wil...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.04.14a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS B202, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14/4/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Mr Bailey, I got your little package.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The supposed <name key="Caesia">Caesia</name> is <name key="Arthropodium%20paniculatum">Arthropodium paniculatum</name>, RBr, a species not previously found in Q.L.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As regards the grasses, it will be best to judge for yourself, when you get the copy of vol. VII in a few months.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7, p 449-670.</p>
               </note> You can then adopt the specific &amp; generic limitations either of Mr Bentham or myself. Bentham has been very <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">liberal</hi>
               </seg>, too much so, in the admission of both genera &amp; species, &amp; his disposition of the genera is to a great measure artificial but not natural, genera of the closest alliance being often placed far apart into different tribes</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <name key="Arthropodium%20paniculatum">Arthropodium paniculatum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Caesia">Caesia</name>
            </p>
         </div>
